post_text:
Remote Learning Plan

March 30, 2020

Hello Hollis Hawks,

Please see the Remote Learning Plan below which will outline how we will proceed until we are able to return to school. Please note that student learning days will occur Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays of each Remote Learning Week. Mondays will be reserved for teacher planning, collaboration, and professional development.

The building will be open for Chromebook checkout Tuesday, March 31 from 9-11 am if you are still in need of a device. Please see our website for requesting meals for next week. At this time, the meal pickup location is Limestone Community High School. If you are having difficulties with technology with Remote Learning, please contact your child's teacher.

We appreciate your support as we continue to strive towards providing the best education possible under these circumstances.

#hawkpride328

shared_text:
Gerald M. Brookhart Arts In Education Spring Celebration
March 19 at 12:25 PM ¬∑

It is with great sadness and heartbreak that the decision has been made to cancel the Gerald M. Brookhart Arts In Education Spring Celebration this year. We are following the direction and guidelines given by the CDC during this time when social distancing is imperative for the safety of not just our community but the entire world. The GMB Arts In Education Spring Celebration directors, board and staff love the students, teachers, directors and schools that have participated in the event for the past 34 years and look forward to next year, our new 35th year of the Gerald M. Brookhart Arts in Education Spring Celebration. Stay home, healthy, positive and creative. Practice your instruments, sing your songs, dance like the world is watching and may the colors be vibrant on your canvas. Keep the music and arts alive in your homes and in your hearts. We love and appreciate you all and will see you next year.

UPDATE: Due to the fluid health situation we are all encountering, we need to move this community effort to the school district versus inside our stores. We are working with school district officials to donate food for those kids who are in need. We will no longer be holding this operation at our store. If your child needs assistance during this time, please contact masscarepeoriacountyIL@gmail.com, or their Facebook page at Mass Care in Peoria County.

We appreciate your understanding!

Mr. Brett is a psychologist, percussionist, AND the uncle of a second grader, and he came to visit our classroom to talk to the students about the role music has played in his life and all the places it has taken him. We ended the class having him demonstrate the drum set since we‚Äôve been talking a lot about percussion this semester. What a fun class - we hope to see him again the next time he‚Äôs in town!

post_text: Over the last couple of weeks, fourth grade explored Simple Machines through innovation, collaboration, technology and creativity! Armed with a Chromebook and foundational knowledge of the six types of Simple Machines, students took part in a #Flipgrid scavenger hunt throughout the school. They recorded brief segments of each simple machine found. Also, students created their own simple machines for our ‚Äúchildren‚Äôs museum‚Äù that needed handicap accessibility. They incorporated inclined planes, pulleys, and wheel and axles. #hawkpride328
